      "picks_file": "picks/picks-2026-06-13-2315.md",
      "why_text": "BMW is facing the same identity crisis every legacy performance brand is wrestling with: how do you sell an electric car to people who bought into the myth of combustion? Ferrari's approach \u2014 preserving iconic model names and emotional heritage rather than rebranding everything with an 'e' prefix \u2014 is becoming the playbook, and BMW adopting it signals the industry is quietly admitting that EV rebrandsstripped too much soul. This is as much a marketing psychology story as it is a car story: performance culture runs on narrative, and the M3 name carries decades of it.",
      "last_escalated_item_ids": [
