      "picks_file": "picks/picks-2026-06-13-2051.md",
      "why_text": "At the six-hour mark of Le Mans, the No. 38 JOTA Cadillac has seized control after the pole-sitting BMW \u2014 widely seen as a genuine title contender this year \u2014 hit serious trouble, reshuffling the Hypercar order dramatically. This is a big moment for Cadillac's endurance racing credibility and a gut-punch for BMW's Le Mans ambitions, which had been building real momentum. With Toyota still lurking, the race is wide open and the next 18 hours are going to be brutal.\n**Update 5:00 PM CT:** BMW has hit back hard: the No. 20 machine has cycled to the front as Hour 7 gets underway and night running begins, suggesting the earlier trouble may have been resolved \u2014 or that strategy and pit sequencing have reshuffled the order once again in BMW's favor.\n**Update 5:00 AM CT:** **Update [Hour 18]:** BMW has reclaimed the lead as a Porsche crash brings out the safety car, compressing the field and setting up a knife-edge final six hours \u2014 with Cadillac right on their heels, the closing stint is shaping up to be a straight fight between the two manufacturers.\n**Update 9:25 AM CT:** **Update [Hour 24 \u2014 FINAL]:** Toyota has won the 2026 24 Hours of Le Mans, outlasting BMW and Cadillac to claim the manufacturer's sixth overall victory at La Sarthe and first in four years \u2014 a stunning late-race result that denies BMW what would have been a landmark win after leading deep into the final stint.",
